    "lyrics": {
      "text": "Jo-seph was a-mazed to see that which tran-scend-ed na-ture’s bounds, for with-out seed, thou, O Maid, didst both con-ceive and bear a Child. And he re-mem-bered the blos-som-ing rod of Aa----ron, the dew up-on the fleece, and the un-burn-ing bush which was not con-sumed, though it was all__ a-flame. Thus, thy pro-tec-tor and be-trothed__ cried, as he bare wit-ness be-fore the priests: A Vir-gin bear-eth, and af-ter child-birth, still re-main-eth a Vir----gin."
    }
  }
}